      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:44:5",
      "text": [
        " أُتِيَ عَلِيٌّ ( عليه السلام ) بِجَارِيَةٍ لَمْ تَحِضْ قَدْ سَرَقَتْ فَضَرَبَهَا أَسْوَاطاً وَ لَمْ يَقْطَعْهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘They came to Ali<sup>asws</sup> with an unmarried girl who had stolen. So he<sup>asws</sup> lashed her with a whip and did not cut her’."
        ]
      }
